hands_on_practices.problem:
In a three-dimensional Euclidean space described by Cartesian coordinates $(x^1, x^2, x^3)$, consider a vector field $C$ whose components $C^i$ are constant real numbers, $C^i = c^i$. Also, consider a symmetric covariant tensor field $T$ of rank 2 (a type (0,2) tensor) whose components in this coordinate system are defined as follows:
$$
T_{ij} =
\begin{cases}
x^i x^j & \text{if } i, j \in \{1, 2\} \\
0 & \text{otherwise}
\end{cases}
$$
Your task is to compute the components of the Lie derivative of the tensor field $T$ with respect to the vector field $C$, denoted by $(\mathcal{L}_C T)_{ij}$.

Express your final answer as the $3 \times 3$ matrix of components $[(\mathcal{L}_C T)_{ij}]$.
